# One-Sentence Guiding Principle
Build a modern, web-based, self-hosted music streaming system that respects user ownership, favors clarity over automation, and grows from manual → assisted → automated workflows without breaking trust.

# Project Purpose & Positioning

* The system is a self-hosted, web-first music streaming platform
* All music is stored locally (user-owned files)
* No dependency on Spotify, YouTube, or external catalogs
* Target users:
  * self-hosters / homelab users
  * privacy-focused users
  * audiophiles
  * developers
  * Success = best open-source option in this niche, not mass-market dominance

# Open-Source Mindset Rules
## Favor:
* clarity over cleverness
* extensibility over completeness
* good defaults over too many options

## Make decisions that:
* reduce contributor friction
* avoid future migrations
* keep the system hackable

# Success Criteria (Guiding Compass)

At every decision point, ask:
* Does this preserve ownership of user data?
* Does this keep source media safe?
* Does this reduce friction for first-time users?
* Does this avoid locking us into assumptions?
* Does this help us compete on UX + correctness, not feature count?

If the answer is “no” → rethink.